work.title: Sonate nr. 2 for violin og klaver, opus 35
Sonata No. 2 for Violin and Piano, Opus 35

history.p: Nielsen's sonata Op. 35 was composed in 1912 for a concert which was planned to take place the following year. According to Nielsen's diary, he started composing before summer 1912. The pianist at the planned concert, Henrik Knudsen, followed the compositional process closely, and according to the correspondence he had Nielsen's draft at his disposal for some periods. The work was completed in September 1912.

annot.p: Programme for an unknown undated concert held after October 1922
